<subSubSection id="D5451843099668D46CD4EBDC77FF6198" pageId="157" pageNumber="158" type="description">
<paragraph id="569604D1D524C62CF05CF408E306E257" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CA230D5FAB4EC1C69DFB931611EF2AB0" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">
Grey spiny undershrub to 60 cm, stems grey-sericeous, spinescent, lateral spines formed from dead peduncles present near branch tips. Leaves sessile, 1-1.7 
<normalizedToken id="FBE4318EA14DFADAB5C6DD69BA437327" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.3-0.6 cm, obtuse, margin entire, base attenuate, grey-sericeous. Flowers solitary (or, fide 
<bibRefCitation id="1661D8C4E38701336632F38F4CDEDBAB" author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
<normalizedToken id="98A9EFC9196B58EB24978A5FB37CB813" originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
(1967)
</bibRefCitation>
, 2-3 in axillary diachasia), axillary, pedunculate; bracts leaf-like; peduncles 3-4 mm, woody; bracteoles c. 1.5 mm, linear, obtuse; pedicels 1.2 mm long, bent at an angle to the peduncle; sepals all similar, 3-6 
<normalizedToken id="A0910A674E90CA57850717B70C1345ED" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-4 mm, obovate, mucronulate, abruptly narrowed at base, adpressed-pilose; corolla 1.6-2.2 cm, white with slight bluish flush, weakly lobed, midpetaline bands pilose; ovary pilose, style pubescent, divided c. 7 mm above base, stigmas 3 mm; capsule and seed not known. [
<bibRefCitation id="A45C22723B9B92F875B173F16A5386BD" author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
<normalizedToken id="6526706AB1BDB6B23133EBA145A2832C" originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
1967
</bibRefCitation>
: 63; 
<bibRefCitation id="6576ED811976F640F972EF9DA591D80D" author="Rechinger, KH" editor="Rechinger, KH" journalOrPublisher="Akademische Druck und Verlagsanstalt, Graz" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 24" refId="B298" refString="Rechinger, KH, 1963. Convolvulaceae. In: Rechinger, KH, Ed., Flora Iranica. Akademische Druck und Verlagsanstalt, Graz: 1 - 24" title="Convolvulaceae." volumeTitle="Flora Iranica." year="1963">Rechinger 1963</bibRefCitation>
: f. 2]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
