<subSubSection id="EBD3F3A9BC7CDC3BF4221EC17FEECF81" pageId="157" pageNumber="158" type="notes">
<paragraph id="59A9B3D1D88751A0C3724835CEC2CCDF" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F5E67712CD2A7481D9C9D393F86DD430" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">
Resembles 
<taxonomicName id="F4570D274DDF6BC8F9A18D587E027C21" authorityName="Burm. f., Fl. Ind. (N. L. Burman) Prodr. Fl. Cap. 47. 1768. (Burman" authorityYear="1768" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus spinosus" order="Solanales" pageId="157" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spinosus">
<emphasis id="68D7634DCA74E87C3C34D4873238F636" italics="true" pageId="157" pageNumber="158">Convolvulus spinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but most easily distinguished by the obovate leaves and all five sepals equal in size and shape.
</paragraph>
